<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Known in the Palearctic Region from the Himalayan countries of Nepal, Bhutan, and the Sikkim Province of India, as well as the Chinese provinces of Guizhou, Jiangxi, Yunnan, and the island of Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation author="Bezdek, A" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="3), Revised and Updated Edition; Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea. Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="367 - 412" refId="B3" refString="Bezdek, A, 2016. Subfamily Cetoniinae. In: Loebl, I, Loebl, D, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 3), Revised and Updated Edition; Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea. Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston: 367 - 412" title="Subfamily Cetoniinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol." year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bezděk">Bezdek</normalizedToken>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). It has only recently been recorded from Hong Kong for the first time (
<bibRefCitation author="Aston, P" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="3 - 4" publicationUrl="http://hkentsoc.org/bulletin/HKEB11(1)April1.pdf" refId="B1" refString="Aston, P, Melsom, P, 2019. Glycyphana horsfieldii (Hope, 1831) a new species of Rose Chafer (Coleoptera, Cetoniina) for the Hong Kong fauna. Hong Kong Entomological Bulletin 11 (1): 3 - 4, http://hkentsoc.org/bulletin/HKEB11(1)April1.pdf" title="Glycyphana horsfieldii (Hope, 1831) a new species of Rose Chafer (Coleoptera, Cetoniina) for the Hong Kong fauna." url="http://hkentsoc.org/bulletin/HKEB11(1)April1.pdf" volume="11" year="2019">Aston and Melsom 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In the Oriental Region, it has been reported from Myanmar, Vietnam, Thailand, Laos, India and Sri Lanka (
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K" journalOrPublisher="Mushi-Sha, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B41" refString="Sakai, K, Nagai, S, 1998. The Cetoniine Beetles of the World. Mushi-Sha's Iconographic Series of Insects (Vol. 3). Mushi-Sha, Tokyo" title="The Cetoniine Beetles of the World. Mushi-Sha's Iconographic Series of Insects (Vol. 3)." year="1998">Sakai and Nagai 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Krajcik, M" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B19" refString="Krajcik, M, 2011. Illustrated Catalogue of Cetoniinae, Trichiinae and Valginae of China (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae). ANIMMA.X, Supplement1/2011, Milan Krajcik, Plzen (Czech Republic), 113 pp + 20 pl." title="Illustrated Catalogue of Cetoniinae, Trichiinae and Valginae of China (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae). ANIMMA. X, Supplement 1 / 2011, Milan Krajcik, Plzen (Czech Republic), 113 pp + 20 pl." year="2011">Krajcik 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
