<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
This species appears to be a new record for the broader region, having also been observed for the first time in Hong Kong only in April 2018 (
<bibRefCitation author="Aston, P" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="3 - 4" publicationUrl="http://hkentsoc.org/bulletin/HKEB11(1)April1.pdf" refId="B1" refString="Aston, P, Melsom, P, 2019. Glycyphana horsfieldii (Hope, 1831) a new species of Rose Chafer (Coleoptera, Cetoniina) for the Hong Kong fauna. Hong Kong Entomological Bulletin 11 (1): 3 - 4, http://hkentsoc.org/bulletin/HKEB11(1)April1.pdf" title="Glycyphana horsfieldii (Hope, 1831) a new species of Rose Chafer (Coleoptera, Cetoniina) for the Hong Kong fauna." url="http://hkentsoc.org/bulletin/HKEB11(1)April1.pdf" volume="11" year="2019">Aston and Melsom 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The subspecies 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. h. subsp. chinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="subSpecies" species="h." subSpecies="chinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">G. h. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miksic, R" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 112" publicationUrl="http://www.repository.naturalis.nl/document/148879" refId="B32" refString="Miksic, R, 1970. Revision der Gattung Glycyphana Burmeister (Coleoptera, Cetoniinae). I. Zoologische Verhandelingen 107: 1 - 112, http://www.repository.naturalis.nl/document/148879" title="Revision der Gattung Glycyphana Burmeister (Coleoptera, Cetoniinae). I." url="http://www.repository.naturalis.nl/document/148879" volume="107" year="1970">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mikšić">Miksic</normalizedToken>
(1970)
</bibRefCitation>
based on its wider extent of the red pronotal margin over the nominal subspecies (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Ma, W" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B27" refString="Ma, W, 1995. Coleoptera: Cetoniidae, Trichiidae and Valgidae. Economic Insect fauna of China 46. Science Press, Beijing" title="Coleoptera: Cetoniidae, Trichiidae and Valgidae. Economic Insect fauna of China 46." year="1995">Ma 1995</bibRefCitation>
), is no longer recognised and has been synonymised with 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. horsfieldii" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">G. horsfieldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jákl">Jakl</normalizedToken>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B26" refString="Loebl, I, Loebl, D, 2016. Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 3), Revised and Updated Edition; Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea. Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston" title="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 3), Revised and Updated Edition; Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea." year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
: 18). Specimens in Macau range in size from approximately 13 to 16 mm TL and from 6 to 8 mm MW. The period of adult activity seems to extend throughout the year, but most observations are from the spring (Apr-May) and autumn (Sep-Oct) months. While the larval stages are not known, adults have been recorded on flowers of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ligustrum sinense" order="Oleales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Ligustrum sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Zanthoxylum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Zanthoxylum avicennae" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="avicennae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Zanthoxylum avicennae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Shefflera" lsidName="Shefflera heptaphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="heptaphylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Shefflera heptaphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1917" baseAuthorityName="Lour." class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Flacourtiaceae" genus="Homalium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Homalium cochinchinense" order="Violales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cochinchinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Homalium cochinchinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
